<title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title>

<statement>
  <p>Clare caminó <m>\frac{3}{4}</m> del sendero que rodea un parque. Tyler caminó <m>\frac{3}{6}</m> del sendero que rodea otro parque. ¿Quién caminó más? Explica tu razonamiento.</p>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample response: I need to know how far it is around the parks. If it is the same distance then Clare walked farther because fourths are bigger than sixths. But maybe the park Tyler was walking around is much longer, like on these number lines, and then Tyler walked farther.</p>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-152497">
    <shortdescription>Number line.</shortdescription>
  </image>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-152498">
    <shortdescription>Number line.</shortdescription>
  </image>
</solution>

</exercise>
